Definition.WordDefinition: Warehouse \Ware"house`\, n.; pl. {Warehouses}. A storehouse for wares, or goods. --Addison. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Warehouse \Ware"house`\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Warehoused}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Warehousing}.] [1913 Webster] 1. To deposit or secure in a warehouse. [1913 Webster]
2. To place in the warehouse of the government or customhouse stores, to be kept until duties are paid. [1913 Webster]
warehouse n : a storehouse for goods and merchandise [syn: {storage warehouse}] v : store in a warehouse
